dialogue: Watch the thorns!
Well, we-we had to go back because I forget my jacket.
Oh man! I did it again!
What?
That's what it sounded like.
Umm, why don't you give me something that would be a good reason and-and then I'll tell you if it's true.
Harder than it sounds. Isn't it?
Umm, listen there's something I think you should know.
Umm, actually I was about to tell you that I was, I was going to get out of it, but hey, if we're just goofing around then uh, maybe I will go out with him.
Feeling a little better sweetie?
Me too.
Hello Dan! I'm really looking forward to Saturday night! Really, really!
Chandler!
So, why wait 'til Saturday, are you free tomorrow?
Oh, great!
Bye Dan!
Great!
Well uh, you and I are just goofing around, I thought, why not goof around with him.
I think you're better than you think you are.
I think you're my favorite.
I don't care.
Phoebe, we are so proud of you! You're amazing!
Chandler, that’s like your fourth cup of coffee!
He’s in a different room! He’s really that loud?
Y’know I used to go out with this guy that was a really light sleeper, and whenever I started to snore, he would just roll me over…
He would just roll me over and I would stop snoring.
Have you guys picked a date yet?

Ugh, she’s upstairs not doing the dishes! And I tell ya something! I’m not doing them this time! I don’t care if those dishes sit in the sink until they’re all covered with—I’ll do them when I get home!
I’ll pick it up for you!
Okay.
Oh my God! Ohh! Look at this one! It’s so beautiful!
Oh, yes, umm, I’m here to pick up a dress that you have on hold.
Emily Waltham.
I am, aren’t I?
Yes?
Phoebe?
Can you just hold on for one minute?
Are you alone?
All right.
Okay, ready?
Okay.
Congratulations!
Okay! My turn! My turn!
This isn’t even my dress.
I’m changing out of this.
In like a half-hour?
Okay, throw it straight this time.
I’m getting married next!!
Yeah. I mean it was kinda fun for a while, but didn’t you start feeling silly?
Oh God.
Hey!
So, is Joey gonna stop snoring?
No, seriously.
Oh my God!
Well, are you asleep right now, Joe? ‘Cause I don’t think you have to wear it unless you are!
Again. Y’know what? I think we all did.
Oh God! He’s gonna come by and borrow some candles for his big date!
No-no, Rachel, don’t get it! He can’t see us!
Hey!
Oh, So you can move them!
It's nice to meet you. Janine...?
Joey, did you even interview this woman before you asked her to move in?
Uh-huh, what exactly did you ask her?
Oh, so you like her too Chandler?
Wait a minute...Joey. Joey you can't ask her out, she's your roommate. It-it'll be way too complicated.
Yeah and you better watch the flirting too, cause you know, in such close quarters, it could be trouble.
Did you also have his album, It's Not Easy Being Green?
So, Phoebe runs weird huh?
Why don't you just be straight with her? Tell her the truth.
I don't know. Rachel I'm-I'm sorry that I hurt your ankles.
We'll see.
Terrible. If-if I want something done right, I have to do it myself. Other people just wreck stuff. I really think I might kill someone tonight.
It's worse. The only thing that's getting me through is knowing that I'm gonna be seeing you soon. I think I may even try to get out of here early.
Well, are you just hanging out with Ross?
What?!
Why is Ross naked?
Naked?
Is it the same thing that Chandler had?
Okay, listen, there's still some of Chandler's medicine under the sink in the bathroom. Bye!
Is it okay for me to come in now?
Why is everything different?
Well, the end table is wrong, The couch looks bizarre and don't even get me started on the refrigerator magnets.
It's okay. Chandler, are you afraid of me or something?

Of course not. I mean gosh, Chandler what you did, it's, it's a wonderful thing and I really appreciate it. I know I have this weird thing where I want everything to be in the perfect place, but I'd never expect you to worry about that.
Of course!
So, did I hear Poconos?
Yeah, that's a big step.
And Monica knows...
Carol called me to thank me for the lasagna, I asked, she told me.
I'm sorry, I'm just excited about being an aunt!
Phoebe, what's the matter?
Phoebe, what is it?
Well, what happened?
Are you sure?
Was it...?
Oh!
So how does this work, you going to balance the plates on these little guys' heads?
Oh, you're right.
Ooh...hey honey, are you all right?
Yes! And that would be a shut-down!
Where are you guys going? Come on, one more game!
Of course! Joey wouldn’t let you have one?
Hey, have you figured out a way to tell him you’re moving out?
Y’know, I really have to tell Rachel, but I… We just have to get it over with! Y’know, the next time we see them we’re just gonna tell them. Okay? That’s it.
Pretty much.
Hi!
Joey, we have something to tell you.
Wait! Joey! Joey! Are you okay?!
Hey Pheebs!
Hey, have you seen Rachel?
I have some pretty exciting news!
No! Chandler and I are moving in together!
Hey!
Well umm, Chandler and I are moving in together.
Ugh, I thought you were Rachel!
I just tell her, I have to get it over with. I told Ross and Phoebe and she’s the only one left!
No.
Really?!
Yeah, he’s gonna work on that.
Soon! I-I just couldn’t before. You saw how upset Joey got! I couldn’t do that to her, she’s my best friend!
I’m not your best friend?
All right, all right, at least I’m prepared.
These aren’t for you! Are you upset?
Rach, there’s something uh, important I have to tell you.
No! But, I’m throwing this shirt away! I think there was a little misunderstanding before.
Umm, when I said that uh, that Chandler and I wanted to umm, live together we meant alone together.
Oh no sweetie, no! This is my fault, I wasn’t clear! I’m really sorry. And listen, you take as much time as you need to move out okay? There’s absolutely no rush.
Okay. Don’t you want a cookie?
Maybe, do you need a tissue?
I made them!
So I, I told Rachel it was just gonna be the two of us.

I mean, all I’m asking for is just a little emotion! Is that too much to ask after six years?! I mean what? Are-are-are Rachel and I not as close as you guys?! I mean do we not have as much fun?! Don’t I deserve a few tears?!! I mean we-we told Joey, he cried his eyes out!
Hey. So um, I was thinking that maybe we should start dividing up our stuff.
Y’know, no point in dragging it out. Dragging out the long process of you moving out and us not living together anymore.
Something to remember me by!
But still, it’s a big change. The end of an era, you might say!
I’m fine! I just, I’m thinking how much it’s an end of era.
An era is defined as a significant period of time. Now, it was significant to me, maybe it wasn’t significant to you!
What is the matter with you?!! Why aren’t you more upset?! Aren’t you gonna be sad that we’re not gonna be living together anymore?! I mean aren’t you gonna miss me at all?!
What’s hard to believe?
Rachel, it’s going to happen. Chandler is gonna move in here.
No-no, wait! Just let me finish, okay? This isn’t something that we just, we just impulsively decided in-in Vegas, this is something we both really want. And it is going to happen.
Yeah, sweetie.
No.
I know!
That place in Vermont? You can take a hint!
Well, can't you just have the party when we get back?
Well, I'm sorry, but Chandler and I could really use a weekend away. You know, to reconnect... emotionally.
All right, we'll stay. We can just drive up after the party.
Believe me, that is not why we won't be doing that!
Hey!
All right... you're right. We're sorry. Now let's wake up Emma and get the fun time started!
Are you freaking kidding me, Green?
So glad you came!

Oh my God, that place has the creamiest frosting! I use to hitchhike there when I was a kid.
Oh, did you do a picture of Emma?
Oh. So nice of her to pull my hair, 'till I dropped the key!
We're Aunt Monica and uncle Chandler, by the way. You may not recognize us, because we haven't spoken to your parents in seventeen years!
Ross, Rachel promised it would be over by now. We seriously have to go, if we want to get to Vermont. I called them and the last train leaves in a half hour.
Alright, 5 more minutes.
No, he didn't! He pretended to be a Quaker to get out of Korea.
Yeah, and we've paid for a room, that we're supposed to be in right now!
No! no! Let's figure out a fair way to decide who's staying.
Ok, how about this: We got wind up toys for Emma for her birthday. We can make them race, and whoever comes in last, stays!
Wha... How the hell is that gonna help?
Now another way to organise your stuffed animals, is by size.
Game?
That's how old you are.
...and head to Canada!
I wasn't. Let's get going!
What about your massage client?
Thanks!
Hey.
How’s the big anniversary dinner?
Ohhh, nice.
Oh no!!
Rachel, you and Mark?!
Hey.
Oh, there’s banana on it.
Oh, good. Thanks.

Okay, all right don’t judge me to much. Okay? Um, but I saw this info-mercial, and um, I swear to you I have never-ever bought anything on TV before, except for this mop. But there was this stuff on leg waxing, it just, it looked so amazing....
Yes! Have you seen it?
I know!!
Hello! Organic substances recently discovered in the depths of the rain forest!
Did that!
No. It was painful. Oh my God , they should call it Pain-zine, now with a little wax.
That’s because their nerves are probably deadened from being so stupid. But hey, y'know if you don’t believe me, please, by my guest.
Now, are you glad we didn’t start with the bikini strips?
Ow!
Ow!! Ow!!
It’s okay, it’s okay.
We were just waxing our legs.
That’s right.
What?
Oh my God.
Because they’ll know we’ve been listening.
What if they don’t?
Hey. It’s three in the morning. They don’t know that I’ve come home yet. You notice how neither one of them are wondering where I am.
And the fact that they're both monkeys.
This wasn't addressed to Days of Our Lives, this is, this came to your apartment. There's no stamp on it, this woman was in our building.
I can't believe Joey's having lunch with his stalker. What i-, what is she like.
Ah, and I mean, he's going out with her? He can not persue this.
Excellent!
Rachel, it's a world where Joey is a neuro-surgeon.
Ross, there he is.
Oh my God, oh my God, oh my God.
Jean-Claude Van Damme. I didn't know he was in this movie, he is so hot.
The muscles from Brussels, wham bam Van Damme, did you see Time Cop?
Rachel, he like, totally changed time.
Oh, yeah.
He could hear me.
Oh Rachel don't, don't you dare, don't, don't. Tell him I cook.
So what'd he say?
Well, thanks anyway.
Rachel if you, if you want to go out with him, you can. Sound like a big jerk to me but if that's what you want to do...
Oh, I'll have an espresso. Oh acutally, I'll get it. If I ask you to, you'll probably end up drinking it yourself.
What did you say?
Ya know, you had no right to go out with him.
You sold me out.
Yes you did. Absolutely.
Did you just flick me?
You flicked me first.
Uh-huh.
OK.
Yes.
Fine,
This is so wild. Ya know, I gotta admit, I was kinda surprised that you agreed to go on a blind date.
Well, what made you make the exception for me?
Say you're sorry.
Say it.
Rachel, you say you're sorry or your sweater gets it.
Say you're sorry.
What're you gonna do?
You don't have the guts.
I'll help you fix your sweater.
I'm sorry that I made you stop seeing him.
OK.
But no. Maybe if I were baking.
Hey!
Yep! You got the tickets?
Okay, if you need the vacuum, it’s in my closet on the left-hand side. Ah, the garbage bags are next to the refrigerator…
Yeah, okay, give that a try!
All right, y’know what? We really are late! Let’s go! Let’s go! Let’s go!!
Chicken Kiev?
It’s nice.
They torn it down a few days early.
Oh my God!
Hey!
Umm…
She said that?!
Why?!
Oh my God. You’re even dumber than I am!
Ross, how long have you been planning this wedding?
Sometimes we were.
Okay.
You’ll see.
Ohh. And I don’t even have a date.
Hey.
Ha ha, a joke that’s funny in all countries.
Well I didn’t want everyone to think I was stupid.
Well, thanks, we like him.
Then why would he say it?
Oh, my mother’s right. I’m never going to get married.
Ohh, Please?! I’m a single mom, with a thirty year old son!!
Yep, yep...You?
Well...I’d better get going.
Well, I love it. I only hope my wedding looks this good.
Stupid.
What were we thinking?
Oh yeah. Definitely.
Hey!
You got out of the whole Tulsa thing?
It's great! How?
No. I can't be away from you for that long.
Yeah, you're my husband. I'm not gonna live in a different state than you for 208 days out of the year.
Honey, thanks for trying to figure out a way, but if you're going to Tulsa, I wanna go with you.
Excuse me?
Why don't you go see Dr. Gettleman?

Oh, maybe he was getting him confused with his childhood therapist.
Yeah, he used to have this recurring nightmare, just really freaked him out.
That I was going to eat him.
Hey!
What are you doing?
That's so sweet. Find anything?
Nothing, huh?
'Slim Pickings'...That is so cheesy.
Honey, that's okay. I actually know this woman, Nancy, who's a restaurant biz head-hunter. Maybe she'll know of something.
Manhattan.

Well, if you really think about it, I mean four days is not that long. I mean, I see you Monday before you go to work, and I see you Thursday when you get back, and I always work late on Tuesdays, so really if you think about it, it's really just one day. And well, if we can't make it one day, we've got real problems my friend.
Really?
That's the nicest anyone has ever said to me!
How was the pediatrician?
Are you serious? You still see Dr. Gettleman?
Where have you been?
Promise to call me when you land.
I love you so much.
Can I talk now?
Joey?

Honey why don’t you go lie down.
Phoebe did the signs!
Phoebe! But I could take one of those little feet and put it in a pita pocket.
Wow, he’s really not letting this go, is he?

Oh my god, I am losing my mind.
Try feeding her again.

Hey.
Okay what’s up

What’s going on?
Excuse me?
Chandler, I don’t even wanna see the musical Oklahoma!

Thank you.
Oh she misunderstood, she thought she was moving to Tulsa.
About a week and a half.
Rach, try holding her a different way.

Say what?
What?
Shhh! We just got her to go to sleep
No.
Hey Phoebe... how you doin'? You feelin' better?
Ok, you got it!
Really? If that's what you want...
Damn it! Rookie mistake!
What are you doing?
Okay if Mike were here what would the two of you be doing?
What are you, animals? It's 4 o'clock in the afternoon!
And now your cell.
This is your cellphone?
This is your current cellphone?
Phoebe, where's your purse?
No, no! Give it to me!
Give it to me!
I'll go in there.
Phoebe come here
Haha!
Haha!
So Phoebe, why are there men's shoes by the door.
Oh, when you get over this breakup we need to go shopping.
Phoebe!
Damnit Phoebe! How did you even call him?
Base Unit! Think Monica! Think!
Look, guys, you can't do this, it's just going to make getting over each other, that much harder.
I've been pretty good!
Oh no no no no... this is dangerous territory. Keep it clean!
You know, on the way over here, I saw this drunk guy throw up. And then a pigeon ate it!
Alright you two, I'm gonna go to the bathroom. Now I don't want anything going on while I'm gone. Here's a few things you can discuss: mucus, fungus and the idea of me and Ross doing it.
Didn't you hear that speech? If you don't kiss him then I will!
Hi, that's what I'm doing for Phoebe!
Excuse me?
Hey, at least I knew where my guy was.
You didn't hear the speech!
Hey, it was very moving! You're just heartless!
You're... weird!
Damn it!
And I blame you too.
Hi, glad you could come.
So, did you know Ross well?
I look like a man??
You are married though.
Awww, look at Aunt Monica's little boy!
Oh, Joey, please tell me you're only donating your time.
OK, we got the cole slaw, we got the buns...
Oh Joey, Melanie called, said she's gonna be late.
Yeah? What does she think of your little science project?
Man's got a point.
Joey... we always know what you mean.
Hey.
You're going to China?
Yeah.
Oh no, she's out having drinks with Carl.
You know, that guy she met at the coffeehouse.
Hey, hold on there, tiger. How's it going? How you holding up?
So, uh, have you ever thought about being there for her?
Y'know, just be there for her.
Think about it.
I can't believe he did this.
I think this is so great! I mean, you and Ross! D-did you have any idea?
From here to the airport?
Rachel, what're you gonna say to him?
Yeah, but if it's good news, you should tell him now.
Uh, so, uh, Rach, uh... do you wanna save this wrapping paper, I mean, it's only a little bit torn... so are you gonna go for it with Ross or should I just throw it out?
Oh my God, me too! Oh! Oh, we'd be like friends-in-law! Y'know what the best part is? The best part is that you already know everything about him! I mean, it's like starting on the fifteenth date!
Another good point.
Why isn't it working out?
Is he not cute enough for you?
Does he not make enough money?
Is there? Is there someone else?
Then why the hell are you dumping my brother?!?
Hey, great skirt! Birthday present?
Oh, from who?
Well, it's the thought. Hey, doesn't Ross's flight get in in a couple hours? At gate 27-B?
Oh, why?
I am not 'so'! OK, I was a teensy bit weird at first, but... I'll be good. I promise.

dialogue: Oh my God!

Yeah!
Phoebe, your face is fine! Come on, none of this stuff is going to happen to you! Stop being such a baby!

No that is not what happened with us. Well, I was umm, I was really sad that night because this guy that I was Ross’s mom.

Really?
Well, not anymore.
I know, I just thought it would be fun.
Drunk enough to know that I want to do this. Not so drunk that you should feel guilty about taking advantage.
Okay!
This doesn’t feel weird!
You’re a really good kisser.
Hm-hmm!

We’re gonna see each other naked.
Do you wanna do it at the same time?
One!
Two!
Eh, we weren’t that close anyway!
Okay, can we change the topic? Because it’s really doing nothing for me.
What?!
No because it-it didn’t seem important.
Noo!! The point is that is was you that was there that night! It is you that I am marrying! It is you that I feel in love with!
Chandler, please! Do you know how unbelievably glad I am that Joey was not there that night?!
Wait Chandler come on, let’s—it’s not a big deal!
Hey-hey.
Honey! Dinner’s ready!
Your favorite!
Yep! And lot’s of it!
Okay, in we go.
Oh, Larry.
Okay, knock yourself out, Larry.
Larry?
Uh, look, Larry honey, umm, I wrote the book on Section 5 and I know that you don't have to wear your hat unless you're in the kitchen.
It's in the kitchen, I'll go get it.
Thanks.
Hmm?
He's not great umm, but he's dealing with it. Oh wait a minute, you're not gonna try…
Right, you only go for them 5 minutes before they get married.
Ohh, fun!
Well, I guess we won't be warming his house.
And you're not gonna do that.
So-so there is no party.
I think so. Se, he-he's not inviting you to his party because he likes you.
Oh, thanks! We'll try to stop by.
You are?
Okay.
What one? You wanted him to invite you to the party and he did it!
Great. So the ball is in his court?
Hey!
I don't know, clean places?
The fake kind!
Okay, great!
Just go over and say hi.
Hey, Danny!
I thought there wasn't a ball?
I think I need a drink.
What was it for?
Wow!
Yeah. But a part of me also can’t wait ‘til it’s over. Chandler and I have this pact not to have sex again until the wedding.
Hey Phoebe, will you give me a hand?
Uh-hmm.
Ross, she’s 25 years old.
Hey!
Subtle guys!
I know you’re planning my surprise bridal shower.
Hey! What did you decide to do about the movie?
That’s what you say about porn.
No! No you should! A lot of major actors do nude scenes! I mean the chance to star in a movie? Come on!
Hey!
Oh boy me too!
Yeah?
The wedding is off, sloppy and immature!
Shrill?! The wedding is back on!

Now Joey, you go down there and you suck up to him. I mean you suck like you’ve never sucked before!
His dancing partner?!

Wait, now so you joined the gym?
Well, you could actually go to the gym.

So you didn’t leave the bank?
Oh my Gosh!
Are you sure you wanna do this?
Whoa!
What are you guys doing here?
Why else would we be here?
This is insane!
What are you talking about? If you get married in Vegas you’re married everywhere.
Yeah!
Hey.
How do I tell Chandler that it’s too soon. It’s gonna break his heart, he’s not gonna think that I don’t love him anymore.
Yes I do!
Oh hi! Hi! Y’know, we were just talking about bacon.
Rach! We weren’t gonna miss our friends getting married!
What are you guys gonna do?
So, what do you think we should do?
That’s a good question. Look umm, last night we let the dice decide. Maybe we should leave it up to fate again. I love you!
All right, eight we get married, but 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 9, 10, 11, 12 we don’t get married.
Ready?
Wow! I can’t believe I actually rolled an eight.
Wait a minute. That wasn’t a hard eight! Last night I rolled a hard eight.
That kid really kicked me hard on the plane.
He took my snack!
Okay! Oh God, y’know what? It’s really bad.
This doesn’t mean anything, does it?
Okay.
No, don’t say it! Don’t even think it!
I’m sick of the signs! It’s too fast, I’m happy the way things are!
I don’t want things to change! Do you?
All right then, then nothing changes! Everything is great! Everything stays the same! And you go unpack because it’s been three days and it’s driving me insane!
Then all your stuff would be here.
Then you’d be going back and forth all the time, I mean it doesn’t make any sense.
Live together? There have been no signs for that.
Yes! Okay! Okay! Wait-wait-wait!
Here’s your key. All right, you have to christen it! Now, go out and come back in!
Ready!
Wait! Oh my God! I can’t get out!
No, it’s not a sign! It’s a very old key!
Oh my God it’s old!
I love you!
No.
You look cute in bubbles.
Chicken? I could eat some chicken.
Wait, what that place, that pub he took us too?
Bodington's!
No, but she likes me. You abandoned her on a plane to Greece.
Rach, that's great! It's so good that you had a good time in Greece!
I'll do it!
Oh, Rachel, sweetie, look, here's a really cute picture of Joey and you at the reception.
Honey, sweetie, by the edges.
Sweetie! Edges! Fingers! Smudgey! Pictures!
Okay. That's okay. I-I know that you're very upset right now. I know, I know that wasn't about me.
You're going to talk to him! Y'know what? We made a deal, I make your decisions and I say you're going to talk to him.
What happened?
See, didn't I tell you?! You're getting over Ross already!
What took you so long?
Oh, good.
Probably some y'know, European good-bye thing he picked up in London.
What is the matter with you?! Do you want to fall into the trap? Do you want to fall into the trap?!
I just ran into Dave and he told me that you blew him off! I mean, you listen to me! Now, I'm calling the shots! I say you leave Ross alone and go get Dave! What the hell were you trying to do?
I make the decisions, and I say no.
You can't fire me. I make your decisions and I say, "I'm not fired!" Ha!
Rachel!! Come on! Let me in!
Rachel locked the door.
Rachel! Let me in! Rachel!
Thank you. Rachel, can I talk to you outside for a sec?
I really need to talk to you.
Okay, I will. Remember that thing that we just discussed that you wanted to do?
All right, Rachel, I know-I know you think I'm crazy, please, before you tell him you love him, just-just try to find one person who thinks this is a good idea. Because I bet you, you can't.
Please!
Joey, I'm in!
Okay, well, why don't we all meet upstairs in an hour?
Come on Rach, let's go.
No! Rachel, you didn't find anyone so you can't tell him.
Okay, Rachel, do you have any idea how painful it is to tell someone that you love them and not have them say it back?
Oh my God! You're water broke!
I can't believe Phoebe's gonna have her babies!
Do you know anything about women?
That's all right.

I’m gonna miss you so much.

No, honey, in a wonderful way. You know what you want now. Most guys don't even have a clue. You are ready to take risks, you are ready to be vulnerable, and intimate with someone.
You made it!
No. Um, I know you like this, and I want you to have it. I think it'll look good in our apartment.
That's fine.

Oh, gosh, this is so weird. I mean, his whole life was in this apartment, and now it's gone. You know, I think it would be nice if we just took a few moments, for Mr. Heckles. I mean, he was kind of a pain, he was, but, he was a person. You're all going to hell.
I have no idea. But look how much they spent!
I know. It's just such reckless spending.
That's me.
Ross, you've got to do something about the humping.
This woman's living my life.

She's living my life, and she's doing it better than me! Look at this, look. She buys tickets for plays that I wanna see. She, she buys clothes from stores that I'm intimidated by the sales people. She spent three hundred dollars on art supplies.
Yeah, well I might be if I had the supplies! I mean, I could do all this stuff. Only I don't.
Oh really? Okay, let's compare, shall we.
Do I go horseback riding in the park? Do I take classes at the New School?
This is so unfair! She's got everything I want, and she doesn't have my mother.
This woman's got my life, I should get to see who she is.
What d'you think?
Oh, no thanks, we're just here to observe.
Okay, d'y'see anybody you think could be me?
Okay, I'm not getting this!
Did you ever feel like sometimes you are just so unbelievably uncoordinated?
Great. It's gym class all over again.
Why don't I just take off my clothes and have a nightmare.
Oh. Monica! ...Hi. I'm Mo- ...nana.
Yeah. It's Dutch.
Um, Pennsylvania Dutch.
Y'know what? After you're with this woman for like ten minutes, you forget all that. I mean, she is this astounding person, with this, with this amazing spirit.
It was so wild. We told them we were the Gunnersens in room six fifteen. Only to find out the Boston Celtics had taken over the entire sixth floor!
...They threw us out! I was thrown out of a hotel! Me!
'Scuse me?
Nononononono. Think who you're dealing with here. I mean, I'm not like you. I-I can't even stand in front of a tap class.
What?
Right. Till I bought a blow dryer, then I was shunned.
Uh-huh.
Wow. Then I would definitely not recommend Mrs. Doubtfire.
Yo- hooo!
Monica and I just crashed an embassy party.
Water rules!
Nope. Going to the Big Apple Circus today.
No, it is me! Y'know, I'm not just the person who needs to fluff the pillows and pay the bills as soon as they come in! Y'know, when I'm with her, I am so much more than that. I'm- I'm Monana!
Helloooo? Yeah. Oh my God. Thanks.
They've arrested Monica.
Hi.
How are you?
Because... I'm Monica Geller. It was my credit card you were using.
I want you to know, it wasn't me who turned you in.
No, thank you! You have given me so much! I mean, if it wasn't for you, I would never have gotten to sing Memories on the stage at the Wintergarden Theater!
I just can't believe you're in here. I mean, what am I gonna do without you? Who's gonna crash the embassy parties with me? Who's gonna take me to the Big Apple Circus?
Well, not... worried, just... wondering.
Not necessarily...
Um, I'm not actually Amish.
Yeah, but at least I'm doing it!
Happy birthday!!!
It’s your birthday!
Chocolate-chip pancakes!
They all came from the list you handed out to us two weeks ago.
Rach, you’re in a great place in your life. Come on, you’ve got a great job! Good friends…
Well, doing nothing on your thirtieth is better than doing something stupid, like Ross.
I can’t believe you bought this.
All right Rach, for what it’s worth, I think that you’re doing great. I mean y’know let’s face it, no one handles this well.
Weren’t you asked to leave sonny?
Noo!!!
Noo!!
Really?! You promise?
Okay. I can do that.
Ross, just forget about it. This guy’s got you totally wedged in.
Yay!
Phil!
All you had to do was buy the card!
I-I-I wanna thank you all for coming. My family and my friends…
Phoebe, y’know why don’t we just go upstairs and have some birthday cake?
Oh man!
He’s gonna eat the cake!

Michael Flatley, Lord of the Dance!

Deal!

Come on!
Come on!
Sandwiches!
Maurice.
And processing.
It’s umm, it has something to do with transponding.
That’s not even a word! I can get this! I can get this!
NOOOOOOOOO!!!!!

Look Rach, we have to move. I mean if they had lost, we would’ve made them get rid of the birds. Right?

Well?

Hey, Rach, can you give me a hand with this box?
I’ll take care of it.

Hey!

Hey, we would still be living here if hadn’t gotten the question wrong!

Great.
Oh, that's there on the bottom, see the manager, Chandler Bing.
A salad? Really I, I could do something a little more complicated if you like.
You got it.
Alright, well I'm tearing the lettuce.
Oh-oh, no no don't worry, I'm gonna wash it.
That's your call.
Well, I thought that I would cut up the tomatos.
They'r alright.
No really, they're OK.
Actually, I was gonna do them jullienne.
Yeah, I think that fifth shower actually got the interview off me.
Oh yeah, well there's the possibility that I won't make rent.
No no no, if I couldn't pay you back right away then I'd feel guilty and tense every time I saw you.
Man, man that is sharp. It must have cost you quite a few debloons.
Hi.
So, what's this.
Wow, that is a surprise. Just one little question, uh, why not Ross's room?
Oh, God forbid.
Where have you been?
No, but that's probably 'cause I haven't asked them yet.
Um, yeah, so uh, uhh, listen, I'm sorry I didn't tell you this before but umm, I, I'm no longer at my job, I, I had to leave it.
Because they made me.
Anything larger back there?
You have dinosaur checks?
Nothin', nothin', hey you're a cheapasaurus. I'm kidding, I'm kidding, thank you, I'm very greatful.
Oh, um, that was my bathing suit from high school. I was uh, a little bigger then.
Hey, you got me, put it in.
You know what this is, this is us getting ready for the prom.
Shut up, the camera adds ten pounds.
Oh, you look so great.
Oops.
Shoot, I think I got mayonaise on you.
Oh, dad, turn it off.
Dad, it is not. What's with the red light?
Ya know, Roy saw Star Wars 317 times. His name was in the paper.
I just told Rachel that Roy touched my boob.
If you're not going then I don't want to go either.
I can't believe you did that.
Mom, I'm hungry.
Alright.
Joey let me ask you a question. What does this light switch do?
Didn’t it drive you crazy to have a switch and not know what it did?
They wouldn’t have put it there if it didn’t do something! How can you not care?
Janice?!
How have you been?
Done?

This switch thing has been driving me crazy. So I turned it off and checked every outlet. Now, four of them don’t work. Which means, one of them has to be controlled by the switch. So, I plugged in things in all four of the outlets that-that make noise, so that way, when I turn it on I just follow the noise and find out which one it is.
He asked you out?!
Saucy!
Electrical plans for the building.
I know that switch does something, okay? So-so I went down to city hall and got these. All I had to do was pay $25 and wait in line for three hours.
Hi!
Oh, just some pictures I made and hung up. I thought they’d brighten up the place. They do don’t you think?
No-no-no, no!
I know that there’s no hole there, I just really liked that picture.
Okay, but there is a wire back there! I mean that switch is connected to something!
I just thought that if I could follow the wire I could find out what it did.
No. It disappears back there behind that baseboard. For a minute there, I thought it went downstairs.
But it didn’t. Say hello to Mrs. Chatracus.
All right. The super couldn’t figure out what it did. A $200 an hour electrician couldn’t figure out what it did. I’ve had seven pretty serious shocks. I officially give up.
I guess Joey was right, it does nothing.
You broke a little girl’s leg?!!
Maybe a Hello Kitty doll, the ability to walk...
No.
Don’t, don’t, don’t, don’t, don’t do this.
What?
No. No, just, just, just a couple more boxes. It-it-it’s no big deal, all right, I’m-I’m cool. You gotta help me out with a couple more boxes!
Christmas cookie?
Is this the one that I threw out last year?
Oh honey, is that ‘cause your Mom died around Christmas?
I'll put a pillowcase over my head.
What's up?
Yeah, you can hear everything through these stupid walls.
Wait a minute, I think Phoebe's right. You know I hear someone else in there with him.
Oh my God, that's Charlie!
I'm not sure about this.
No I'm not sure that it's the best way to hear everything. Someone get me a glass!
What?
I can't believe this. Rachel and Joey?
I'm on it!
I think I hear curtains closing...
Bedsprings, unmistakable!
Okay, I've had it with the hair jokes. Tomorrow morning, before we leave, I'm going to the salon.
Honey, if you know it through a wall, you know it too well!
Other wall, people! Other wall!
Yeah, but he wants to talk to you before anything really happens with her. And as his friend, I mean, don't you think he deserves the same from you?
Check it out!
What do you think?
Don't you just love it?
Yeah!
It's "Bolero" from "10".
You what? You said you liked them.
Fine, so you don't like them. Everybody else does.
And the eye!
Not really.
I have a problem.
Well, I was dancing around, and singing "No Woman, No Cry" and I got stuck.
Yeah, I tried to gnaw myself free.
Sure, what do you have in mind?
Really? I don't really feel like it.
Okay, I just don't get why you like it so much.
Then what's the problem?
What, forget it!
Joey, you know, maybe your just not used to kissing men, maybe you just tensed up a little, maybe that's what you need to work on.
Woo-hoo, stuud!
Woo-hoo, geeek!
Please!
What are you talking about? What wedding?
Nooo! Never! I mean, we're living in the moment. God, it is so nice for once to not have to get all hung up on 'Where is this going?'
Could not be more terrified.
Hey, you know I got a question for ya. Just a little thing, no pressure.
Did you ever, uh, like, think about the future?
Yeah, am I in it?
Oh God, you are about to get sooo lucky.
Keep talkin'.
Okay, so, uh, we're in France, we're making the toast. Do you see a little bassinet in the corner?
Not a basset, a bassinet.
Well, I just think the baby would keep falling off the dog. Do you, uh, do you , do you not see kids in our future.
Uh-huh.
That's Great. You know we don't need to talk about this now. Really, I mean this is, is so way, way, way, in the future, I'm talkin' hovercrafts and apes taking over the planet.
So, I read this article in the paper the other day that says you're not supposed to throw rice at weddings, because when pigeons eat rice it kills them.
Oh, absolutely. Yeah, you know I'm not even thinking about that thing that we're not supposed to think about.
Okay, one more, please. Come on, I'm gonna get it in this time, I will.
You'll do what?
Oh my God!
Really?
You're the most wonderful man. And if you hadn't of said 'if I have to' like seventeen times, then I'd be saying 'okay, let's do it.'
Oh my God, I can't believe what I'm getting ready to say. I wanna have a baby, but I don't wanna have one with someone who doesn't really wanna have one.
Hi!
Oh that’s great!
I mean think about all the money that you’re gonna make!
Well, her father pays you for baby-sitting right?
Oh, I love museums!
Soakin’ up all the culture.
Where do you want to start?
Yeah!
What?! Are you crazy?! I’m not getting married! I’m not even engaged.

Oh please, he didn’t hear it! He didn’t hear it!!

I know.

The guy who made these hates feet and wants to see them die!

I-I don’t-I don’t think that I’m gonna wear the boots tonight.
Well y’know, I’m just-I’m just worried that bosses will see them and think they pay you too much money. Or! Or your assistant will see them and-and want a raise!

What are you being such a weenie for? So he has a Barbi, big deal. You used to dress up like a woman.
Well, you used to dress up in Mom's clothes all the time.
The big hat, the pearls, the little pick handbag.
How can you not remember? You made us call you...Bea.
Wasn't there a little song?
'I drink tea.'
'....Won't you, won't you, won't you.... '

Yeah sure, nature called, she wanted to see who else did.
You’re on the phone!
Oh well, it’s not so bad.
Isn’t that mine?
Hey!
Wow! So, now you’re going on a date with this girl?
You’re right, I’m sorry. It’s not like you’re y’know, going out with an ex-girlfriend.
You dated her!
All right, well why don’t I go out with an ex-boyfriend and do Joey a favor?!
Now, this is last minute so I want to apologize for the mess. Okay?
I know! Now look, there’s only one problem though. There’s only room for one, so I guess one of you will have to stay at Joey’s.

Now there you go! I wouldn’t want my best guest to strain her eyes!
Does that smell bother you?
Well you let me know if you can, because y’know I can bake a pie to cover it.
Okay!
So it’s okay to date a student.
Well Ross, you be careful now. You don’t want to get a reputation as y’know Professor McNailshisstudents.
Joey that is so sweet.
What?! You’re going out with her again!
Joey! You didn’t even know her!
Hey! How’s it goin’?
Yes it has! I made cookies!
But you should eat them now because they’re hot from the oven.
Okay!
You’re kidding!
Ross!
Joey, why don’t you put them in the lost and found?
Oh my God, what a fun day! That sounds great!
Don’t worry about it Phoebe, we’ll absolutely do it.
Pheebs, how’s it going?
Nope, sound like me. Pheebs, it’s going great. Look at Chandler with little baby girl Chandler.
What do you mean?
This is so great! This is exactly how we set the plates at the restaurant.
Oh yeah, I got soap and sponges and rags and Carnuba wax and polishing compound.
I know. But umm, one time there was this really dirty car in front of the building, so I washed it.
And six others.
Yeah, two hours, a lifetime that’s the same.
Chandler, what are you doing? That thing can put someone’s eye out!
Oh it’s so cute. I wonder what age it is when you stop being able to put both legs over your head.
How are you still single?!
Good. What made you change your mind?
And people will think you own a Porsche because you’re wearing the clothes?
Joey, you know you don’t actually have one.
All right, that’s it, we’re going to the emergency room.
The babies are asleep, I’m sure you’ll be okay on your own for a while!
He’s got something plastic lodged in his throat, we’ve got to go to the hospital.
Oh my God.
Phoebe, what, what happened here?!
But my apartment!
But the mess!
You’re right, you’re right I shouldn’t freak out. ‘Cause this is what will happen when you and I have babies! When will that be?!
What are you talking about?
You were invited?!
My God, I can’t believe this! I mean I knew that mom and dad were invited, but I thought that was it! I mean from the ages 7 to 9 Frannie and I were inseparable!

Yeah, well you call her and tell her that y’know when we were kids her precious little Frannie tried to undress me several times, okay? And if I hadn’t have stopped her, there probably wouldn’t even be a wedding to go too.
Joey, that paper’s like a year old!
Hey.
Joan?
Wait a minute, you got Ross Gellar and guest?! I wasn’t invited and you got "and guest?!"
Wait a minute, y’know, you’re bringing me!
Why not?!
Because! She’s my cousin. I mean, we grew up together! We’re family y’know? Well that’s important to me.
David who?
Phoebe, can I talk to you for a second?
What are you doing?
So! He’ll understand!
God, you are so strong.
I’m Monica Gellar. Who do you know the bride and groom?
Used to work with her. Used to! I’m a relative and I didn’t get invited! A blood relative! Blood!!
Okay, you’re fine.
Frannie was the one who found your Playboys and showed them to mom.
Am I doing here? Why? Surprised to see me? Ross brought me. How do you like that?!
Oh wait I forgot my wrap.
